1.Input validation : Use proper input and valid them.

2. Annotation : First of all add appropriated annotation and import package accordingly because 
there are multiple package, If you are importing wrong package then you will be not able to get output.

3. Security : Api should be secure. Authentication and Authorization is very important part of your api, 
please ensure only authorized user can access your data.
This can be achieved through Spring Security.

4. Testing : Api should be tested to ensure the expected output. There are multiple kind of testing
like unit testing, integration testing and etc.

5.Exception Handling and Error handling : Api should have proper exception and error handling. 

6. Documentation : Documentation is very important so other can understand what you did and why.







